  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Colorectal cancer (CRC) is the second common cause of death in the Western world, and is very
      increasing in Japan. Fecal occult blood test (FOBT) is used routinely for CRC screening,
      which has been shown to reduce the incidence, morbidity, and mortality of CRC. However, there
      is a need to develop a novel method to improve sensitivity. The investigators reported that
      Fecal COX-2 assay, one of fecal RNA test, is potentially useful for colorectal cancer
      screening (Gastroenterology 127; 422-427, 2004). So the investigators planed to compare fecal
      RNA test with FOBT for detecting colorectal cancer and adenoma.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
